# 9. Beginner Mistakes

### Mistake 1

Thinking Internet and network mean the same thing.

Wrong.

The Internet is a network.

Not every network is the Internet.

---

### Mistake 2

Thinking an IP address is permanent.

Wrong.

It usually changes over time.

---

### Mistake 3

Thinking a MAC address equals an IP address.

Wrong.

MAC = hardware identity.

IP = network location.

---

### Mistake 4

Thinking ping measures Internet speed.

Wrong.

Ping measures **latency** (round-trip time), not download bandwidth.

---

### Mistake 5

Thinking every device has a public IP.

Wrong.

Most home devices use private IPs behind a router.

