# 12. Career Relevance

Every cybersecurity role depends on networking.

| Role | Why networking matters |
| --- | --- |
| SOC Analyst | Investigates suspicious network traffic and alerts. |
| Incident Responder | Traces how attackers moved through networks. |
| Penetration Tester | Understands network layout before testing defenses. |
| Malware Analyst | Examines how malware communicates with remote servers. |
| Digital Forensics | Reconstructs events using network logs. |
| Cloud Security Engineer | Secures communication between cloud resources. |
| Network Security Engineer | Designs and protects routers, switches, VPNs, and firewalls. |

In interviews for junior cybersecurity roles, networking is one of the first technical foundations employers expect.

